 :tx/rationale "Create task: CCE-3: Innate concept schemas — Piagetian sensorimotor reflexes for knowledge bootstrapping. CONTEXT: A fresh store starts from epistemic zero. DOGFOOD-2 Orientation scored 3.3/10 because agents had no initial structure. Piaget's genetic epistemology: children start with INNATE SCHEMAS (grasping, sucking, looking) that provide scaffolding for concept formation. Braid needs the equivalent: universal cognitive schemas that structure exploration before domain-specific knowledge exists. RATIONALE: Five schemas are universal for understanding ANY structured artifact: components (parts and boundaries), dependencies (how parts relate), invariants (what should hold true), patterns (recurring regularities), anomalies (deviations). These emerge from braid's 42 sessions of self-development — the distillation of how agents actually explore codebases. They are the project's accumulated self-knowledge transmitted as the genome for offspring sessions. APPROACH: (1) Define 5 innate concept entities in the policy manifest (bootstrap.rs or policy.rs). Each has: :concept/name (e.g., 'components'), :concept/description (e.g., 'Parts of the system and their boundaries — packages, modules, crates, files'), :concept/embedding (pre-computed from description text via embed_text), :concept/member-count 0, :concept/created-at (genesis timestamp), :concept/innate true (Boolean flag distinguishing innate from emergent). (2) At braid init, transact these 5 concept entities as part of the policy manifest transaction. They are datoms like everything else (C1 compliant). (3) The 5 schemas come from the default software policy manifest (bootstrap.rs). Different domains can define different innate schemas in their policy manifest (C8 compliant). A research lab might have: hypotheses, experiments, observations, instruments, anomalies. A compliance team: regulations, controls, evidence, gaps, exceptions. (4) Pre-compute embeddings for the 5 default descriptions and hardcode as byte arrays (avoids requiring the embedding model at init time). The embeddings are ~1KB each, static, and can be regenerated if the model changes. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After braid init, 5 innate concept entities exist in the store. (B) Each has all schema attributes including :concept/innate = true. (C) Innate concepts have pre-computed embeddings (not zeros). (D) First braid observe auto-matches against innate concepts (cosine > threshold for relevant text). (E) Non-software policy manifests can define different innate schemas. (F) Innate concepts participate in the same crystallization pipeline as emergent concepts (no special-casing). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (innate schema definitions), crates/braid/src/bootstrap.rs or crates/braid/src/commands/init.rs. DEPENDS-ON: CCE-2 (concept entity schema). TRACES-TO: ADR-FOUNDATION-013 (Policy Manifest — innate schemas are policy-layer configuration)."
